gomodel:SYNGO_1101  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Application of noradrenaline to cultured hippocampal neurons induces a reduction in the frequency of miniature EPSCs (Fig 4). Application of the selective alpha1-agonist cirazoline also induced a reduction in the mEPSC frequency, but no change in mEPSC amplitude (Fig. 4d, f). These findings indicate that presynaptic G-Protein coupled Alpha1-adrenergic receptors modulate synaptic transmission upon activation.. Experimental description: For the preparation of hippocampal cultures, hippocampi were carefully dissected from E18 rat embryo brains" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" ;
        dc:date           "2018-05-29" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_1101" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

